<div id="review_147643120" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/147643120" />
    <a title="Karen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/967701-karen"><img alt="Karen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1535032331p2/967701.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/147643120?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen" href="/user/show/967701-karen">Karen</a>
      </span>

          marked it as to-read




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/967701-karen?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer147643120" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13675781372849475877">This is a tale from more recent times. It is about 3 sailors who find themselves in the middle of an unexpected hurricane. 1 of the sailors is a personal friend of the author and his story sounds like the most sad, yet heroic story of all.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


